Janene Christiansen is the Registrar and Associate Vice-President, Strategic Enrolment at George Brown College. She has extensive experience leading teams in various registrarial roles, including admissions, assessment, convocation, fees and scheduling, financial aid, systems and reporting, and registration and audit. Janene started her career at George Brown in 2003 as an operations manager in the Registrarâ€™s office. She spent more than a decade in registrarial leadership roles at other post-secondary institutions before returning to George Brown in 2022.

Janene has been recognized with several awards for her leadership, including the Sheridan Inspirational Leader Award and the President's Distinguished Administrative Staff Award from Humber College. She holds a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science and Psychology from the University of Western Ontario.
